967
00:58:42.322 --> 00:58:46.042
of colorectal cancer patients shows really remarkable responses to

968
00:58:46.582 --> 00:58:50.522
immunotherapy, in this case, checkpoint inhibitor anti-PD-1 therapy.

969
00:58:51.922 --> 00:58:55.242
This particular subset are mismatch repair deficient rectal cancer

970
00:58:55.342 --> 00:58:58.722
patients that show 100% complete response rates to

971
00:58:58.742 --> 00:59:01.322
PD-1 blockade in locally advanced

972
00:59:01.332 --> 00:59:02.802
disease.

973
00:59:03.642 --> 00:59:07.622
So these are tumors that are very sizable, that already grew into the outermost

974
00:59:07.662 --> 00:59:08.622
layers of the rectum

975
00:59:09.602 --> 00:59:12.802
and maybe spread to lymph nodes. And within just a few months,

976
00:59:13.182 --> 00:59:16.702
this tumor with just immunotherapy alone essentially melts away.

977
00:59:17.442 --> 00:59:21.322
This is incredibly remarkable for the patients because prior standard of care

978
00:59:21.362 --> 00:59:25.192
for these patients was a combination of neoadjuvant chemotherapy, radiation, and

979
00:59:25.222 --> 00:59:25.742
then surgery.

980
00:59:27.902 --> 00:59:31.822
So this is the example where we wanted to understand how immune responses

981
00:59:31.862 --> 00:59:34.102
can be actually successful in tumors.

982
00:59:34.142 --> 00:59:37.742
And we contrast that to the vast majority of colon cancer patients,

983
00:59:37.822 --> 00:59:41.602
85% of all colon cancer patients, that do not have this

984
00:59:41.642 --> 00:59:45.062
particular subtype. Instead, they're so-called mismatch repair

985
00:59:45.142 --> 00:59:48.502
proficient tumors, and they essentially have no response to

986
00:59:48.542 --> 00:59:49.182
immunotherapy.

987
00:59:50.862 --> 00:59:54.722
So to understand how immune responses work in these two different settings, we did

988
00:59:54.742 --> 00:59:58.302
a large single cell RNA sequencing study on 35 of these

989
00:59:58.342 --> 01:00:02.202
immunotherapy responsive patients and 29 of the immunotherapy

990
01:00:02.262 --> 01:00:03.042
non-responsive

991
01:00:03.842 --> 01:00:07.812
subtype of colon cancer, performed single cell RNA sequencing

992
01:00:07.842 --> 01:00:10.862
on around 400,000 individual transcriptomes.

993
01:00:11.142 --> 01:00:15.102
We clustered that to discover the different cell types and states and gene

994
01:00:15.182 --> 01:00:15.602
programs.

995
01:00:16.562 --> 01:00:20.342
And then we used computational approaches to predict how these

996
01:00:20.362 --> 01:00:24.282
different cell types and gene programs work together as functional units.

997
01:00:25.962 --> 01:00:29.242
And the result of this computational analysis actually was

998
01:00:29.262 --> 01:00:33.002
satisfyingly simple because we picked up on essentially three

999
01:00:33.042 --> 01:00:34.042
major immune hubs.

1000
01:00:35.082 --> 01:00:37.582
The first is what I would

1001
01:00:38.562 --> 01:00:42.362
call an inflammatory hub. So this is an NF-kappa B

1002
01:00:42.482 --> 01:00:46.402
type of acute inflammatory reaction that brings myeloid

1003
01:00:46.442 --> 01:00:48.242
cells and granulocytes into the tumors.

1004
01:00:49.012 --> 01:00:51.942
The second I would refer to as tissue remodeling hub.

1005
01:00:52.782 --> 01:00:56.742
This is connected to this acute inflammatory hub and is characterized

1006
01:00:56.782 --> 01:01:00.762
by growth factors, angiogenesis, so a lot of things that we think might help

1007
01:01:00.802 --> 01:01:01.622
the tumor to grow.

1008
01:01:02.582 --> 01:01:06.362
And then the third one was especially interesting to us, and we named it

1009
01:01:06.422 --> 01:01:10.262
antitumor immunity hub because this one was only present in the

1010
01:01:10.322 --> 01:01:14.242
patients with this immunotherapy responsive subtype, this mismatch repair deficient

1011
01:01:14.282 --> 01:01:14.692
subtype.

1012
01:01:16.022 --> 01:01:19.502
And this hub was characterized by T cells, so the killers of our

1013
01:01:19.542 --> 01:01:23.332
immune system, especially activated and exhausted versions of that,

1014
01:01:23.922 --> 01:01:27.902
as well as interferon stimulated gene programs in myeloid cells and also the cancer

1015
01:01:27.942 --> 01:01:28.222
cells.

1016
01:01:29.652 --> 01:01:33.642
And so this work was published, but today I'm going to show

1017
01:01:33.702 --> 01:01:37.582
you unpublished work building on these, where we now took

1018
01:01:37.842 --> 01:01:41.542
these predictions and actually mapped these immune hubs

1019
01:01:42.002 --> 01:01:45.942
on tumor tissues with the idea that maybe we can

1020
01:01:46.082 --> 01:01:49.822
